5|$|Crean's {{older brother}} was Cornelius Crean, <b>a</b> <b>sergeant</b> in the Royal Irish Constabulary (RIC). Cornelius {{was based in}} West Cork, where he served with the RIC during the War of Independence. Sgt. Crean was killed during an IRA ambush near Upton, West Cork on 25 April 1920.|$|E
